1.title: Secrets of the Jars
1.plot: The escape of a cache of new Jar Dwellers has Ooble, Crunch, Barka, Sophie and David trying to find them before Van Riceberger.

2.title: Wrestlemaniac
2.plot: With Crunch as his coach, David must beat Van Riceberger to get on the wrestling team. Crunch teaches him special moves to win.

3.title: Changkovsky
3.plot: Van Riceberger believes Chang is a musical genius and enters him into Silly Sausage's talent show.

4.title: Madame Ooble
4.plot: Ooble believes she has clairvoyant powers when she finds one of Snapp's eggs acts like a crystal ball.

5.title: Who Dairies Wins
5.plot: The Jar Dwellers need to kidnap Van Riceberger's stinky cheese to re-grow Slipp's amazing shell.

6.title: Completely Rocknuts
6.plot: A short course lets Sophie and Chang determine the relative sanity of Grill and Van Riceberger.

7.title: Crunch P. Crunchington
7.plot: When Silly Sausage doesn't turn up to Crunch's birthday party, Sophie, David and the Jar Dwellers team up to give him the best birthday ever.

8.title: Crunch Drunk Love
8.plot: Crunch takes over hosting the Kutes from Barka, but he quickly finds he can't keep up with their party pace.

9.title: Parasite Paradise
9.plot: A worm-like parasite uses Van Riceberger as a host and sets him on a quest to locate very small Jar Dwellers.

10.title: Testing Times
10.plot: After distracting David from school with a series of false emergencies, the Jar Dwellers discover Slipp is key to getting him an A.

11.title: Law of Relative to Tea
11.plot: The arrival of rich Aunt Mimi pits Van Riceberger against Chang in a bid for her attention and fortune.

12.title: Portrait Power
12.plot: Moosh impersonates Van Riceberger's forebears to save the Jar Dwellers' dwindling food supply.

13.title: Huggaconda
13.plot: A Jar Dweller is mistaken for an anaconda, causing panic and a lock down in the school.

14.title: Eggsellent Adventure
14.plot: Van Riceberger mistakenly suspects a large egg belongs to a Jar Dweller, until he tries to incubate it and it melts.

15.title: Ka-Chang!
15.plot: Chang wins Silly Sausage's Snaglotto and reverses roles with Van Riceberger.

16.title: Long Lost Aunt Snootasha
16.plot: Sophie and David discover a plot to demolish the glasshouse, so they send in Snoot and Grill to stop Van Riceberger's plans.

17.title: Mr Uniwurst
17.plot: Crunch signs up for Mr Uniwurst's bodybuilding course to compete with Grill's outstanding abilities.

18.title: Forget Me Snot
18.plot: A strange phenomenon causes explosive sap to seep from Barka's feet. Sophie searches for a rare potato berry cure.

19.title: Van Liceberger
19.plot: Free combs from Monsieur Chang infect the whole school and Van Riceberger with head lice.

20.title: Brother Crunch
20.plot: Van Riceberger discovers a wood-munching Jar Dweller, while Sophie and David blame Crunch for a power outage.

21.title: Chang Sells Out
21.plot: A jack hammering Jar Dweller arrives to upset the pecking order.

22.title: Party Pooper
22.plot: It's surprise party time as Van Riceberger tries to find out where Chang has thrown one for him.

23.title: Van Niceberger
23.plot: A strange drink transforms Crunch into a superhero, with Moosh as his sidekick, as they fight to save the school.

24.title: Repulsive Hero
24.plot: A strange toxic drink transforms Crunch into a superhero, with Moosh as his sidekick, as they fight to save the school.

25.title: News of the Weird
25.plot: Extra, extra, read all about it. David new editor on school paper.

26.title: Send in the Clones
26.plot: Green clones of Crunch, Chang and Van Riceberger sprout after they eat fruit and seeds from an over-fertilised Barka.

27.title: Relatively Seeking
27.plot: A bump on the head sends Sophie delusional, making her believes she's part of the Van Riceberger clan.

28.title: Fossil Fools
28.plot: Van Riceberger's rocket induced landslide reveals a strange Jar Dweller shaped fossil that fascinates Slipp.

29.title: Much A-Goo About Nothing
29.plot: In a lab mishap, Professor Chef invents the new must-have toy, GOO. Once opened it becomes stinky, gassy goo.

30.title: Dude, Where's My Curse?
30.plot: David helps Chang rid himself of the Chang Family Curse, but his efforts backfire when he gets cursed.

31.title: Too Much Exposition, Kid
31.plot: It's a case of puppy love when Expo Kid and Sophie partner up on an assignment from Van Riceberger.

32.title: Great Gateau Bake Off
32.plot: Things heat up in the kitchen as Professor Chef takes on David for the Great Gateau Bake Off.

33.title: A Case of Mislaid Eggs
33.plot: In a no-holds-barred whodunnit, Sophie and David investigate the disappearance of Snapp's latest clutch of eggs.

34.title: Natural Election
34.plot: Sophie has trouble competing with Van Riceberger as they each campaign to be President of the Science Club.

35.title: Bed-Lam
35.plot: The cave becomes overcrowded when all the Jar Dwellers hide there to escape Van Riceberger's latest tracker.

36.title: Ooble of the Opera
36.plot: Princess Ooble is in shock when she finds out Van Riceberger will play the lead role of her life story.

37.title: Barka to the Future
37.plot: When Barka hijacks a Jar Tracker time machine, he has no idea whether is he at yesterday, today or tomorrow.

38.title: Spooky Sausage
38.plot: The Jar Dwellers confront their inner fears with the help of David's dice and his new Spooky Sausage board game.

39.title: Same Same But Different
39.plot: Sophie tests the Kutes for their twin factor and finds that they are the same same but different.

40.title: Happy Grillmore
40.plot: Decked in crazy golf attire, Grill hits a hole-in-one to beat Van Riceberger for the Silly Sausage Golf Classic.

41.title: Not So Well Room
41.plot: Barka proves his leadership skills when he rescues Ooble from a fall down the old well shaft.

42.title: Dung and Dusted
42.plot: With the help of a secret Tom Bowler, David challenges Van Riceberger to a rigged marbles tournament.

43.title: A Puzzling Page
43.plot: An invisible ink message in the Big Book predicting a solar eclipse causes pandemonium in the cave.

44.title: Curse of the Were-Croc
44.plot: In the search for her chosen one, Snapp mistakes a crocodile-shaped Jar Tracker for her egg-mate.

45.title: Silly Sausage Sizzle
45.plot: While guest of honor at the Silly Sausage Sausage Sizzle, Silly Sausage gets his buns burnt.

46.title: Where is Professor Chef
46.plot: Inspired by his latest detective comic, David sets out to solve the missing Professor Chef mystery.

47.title: For the Record
47.plot: World records tumble as the Jar Dwellers help Barka to make a name for himself.

48.title: It's the Thought that Counts
48.plot: A strange mind reading machine from long ago forces Sophie to reveal the Jar Dwellers to Chang.

49.title: If the Shell Fits
49.plot: It's a Cinderella story when Van Riceberger tries to find the Jar Dweller that fits the shell that was left behind.

50.title: Beans means Heights
50.plot: A jar of "magic" beans sends VR through the roof, and Chang on a mission to destalk the problem.

51.title: Chang is as Good as a Holiday
51.plot: Chang takes a well-deserved long service break, but he suffers Van Ricebergerinterruptus.

52.title: Van Do Over
52.plot: An accidental ingestion of Chang's furniture rejuvenator turns Professor Ludwig Van Riceberger into young Luddy.

1.title: New Territory, Hide 'n' Seek
1.plot: Sophie and David are bewildered by an argument that sees Ooble, Crunch and Barka risk all for a plot of their own. The Jar Dwellers use new SOS camouflage skills to escape to the school's Halloween Fair.

2.title: Next Trick, Junk Food Jumble
2.plot: Sophie talks David into using his magic skills to return the Jar Dwellers to their homelands. Chang's deep-fried pizzas cause mutations in the Jar Dwellers that Sophie can't work out.

3.title: Wooly Yarn, Water Logged
3.plot: Sophie's plan to study the Jar Dwellers winter growth nearly comes unstuck at the ice skating rink. Sophie's cure for Barka's itchy skin sees him survive the river, rapids, and a working saw mill.

4.title: Arty and Craftier, Well Well Well
4.plot: Sophie takes credit for the reactions to David and the Jar Dwellers' abstract entry to the Art Show. The lure of Silly Sausage in 3D has the Jar Dwellers risking all for snacks and a night of laughs.

5.title: Baby Barka, Empty Nesters
5.plot: In a classic mix up, Barka believes a bonsai is his cloned child until Ooble breaks the bad news. A camping trip to cure Barka's sleepwalking goes awry when he is inhabited by a colony of birds.

6.title: Night of the Living Dread, Three Ring Riceberger
6.plot: Sophie's horror movie night babysitting gig gets undermined by Chang's own horror show. Red noses from an allergy help the Jar Dwellers clown their way to top billing at a traveling circus.

7.title: Ooble Takes Flight, Who's a Silly Sausage
7.plot: Ooble takes advantage of Sophie's Kite-a-thon to realise her dream of flying like a bird. Crunch loses the Silly Sausage lookalike contest but wins the respect of his hero.

8.title: Heat Wave, 1001 Crunches
8.plot: During a heat wave, Van Riceberger uses water rations and an inflatable pool to flush out the Jar Dwellers. Crunch's insatiable appetite gets him into trouble with Ooble, Barka and Dog Catcher Chang.

9.title: Silence of the Glams, Professor Chef
9.plot: A flat out Nurse Chang deals with a flu epidemic and stray tissues as a bout of laryngitis shuts up Ooble. Chang's Professor Chef TV Show inspires Ooble to prove to Sophie she can cook to survive.

10.title: Lie Detector Test, Rocketing Home
10.plot: Sophie uses the Lie Detector Jar Tracker to get to the truth of Ooble's missing boomerang. Van Riceberger's spacecraft rockets the Jar Dwellers to what they think is a new planet.

11.title: Pest in Show, Spring Clean Fever
11.plot: Sophie risks the Jar Dwellers when she enters them in Van Riceberger's Pet Show trap. A white football releases Ooble's mothering instincts when she mistakes it for her egg.

12.title: Shelf Sufficiency, Fire Drill
12.plot: Sophie's master plan to grow their own food backfires when Barka over stimulates the crop. David and Sophie's fire drill gets Barka hot under the collar and over conscientious as a Fire Marshall.

13.title: Shock Therapy, Chickening Out
13.plot: A cleaning accident sees Van Riceberger come to grips with a personality change. Van Riceberger tricks Sophie with an egg nurturing scheme that unleashes Ooble's jealous side.

14.title: Brotherly Love, Filling in the Gaps
14.plot: When an old note from the BigBook suggests that Ooble and Crunch may be related, Crunch is delighted but Ooble is mortified. Despite Sophie's best intentions, Crunch's stomach reacts violently to her new health diet.

15.title: Negative Exposure, Ooble's New Owner
15.plot: David documents Sophie's wild food eating program, but loses his camera containing an image of Ooble that Chang ultimately finds. At the local carnival, Ooble hides on the plushee prize shelf but is won by Fontana and taken to her home.

16.title: Ooble Pox, Murder in the Dark
16.plot: Ooble wakes to a bout of pox over her face and body, which has Sophie, David, Crunch and Barka searching for a cure. Van Riceberger creates a Frankenstein-esque robot that kidnaps Barka to please its master.

17.title: Lightning Tracker, Life in the Fast Lane

imdb.plot outline: Two siblings, Sophie and David, discover and release three amazing creatures from special science jars hand made by famous naturalist Albert Derwent. Ooble, Crunch and Barka are not ready for repatriation so Sophie, with the help of Derwent's Big Book, introduces them to her "Survival of Species" program. They learn to avoid Professor Van Riceberger, his Jar Trackers and his assistant Chang. The creatures have no plans to return home. They're out and there is no going back.
